{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the 'rawcontinue' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for 'continue' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"4598335":{"pageid":4598335,"ns":0,"title":"Obnoxio the Clown","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"'''Obnoxio the Clown''' is a [[character (arts)|character]] in the [[Marvel Comics]] humor magazine ''[[Crazy (magazine)|Crazy]]''.<ref name=\"obnoxio\">[http://daveslongbox.blogspot.com/2005/04/obnoxio-clown-marvel-comics-1983.html Obnoxio the Clown] information, Accessed August 2008.</ref>\n\n==Character==\nObnoxio was portrayed as a slovenly, vulgar, cigar-puffing middle-aged man in a torn and dirty [[clown suit]], with a dyspeptic and [[Cynicism (contemporary)|cynical]] attitude.\n\n==Comic book==\n''Obnoxio the Clown'' was also the title of a one-shot [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] [[comic book]] that was published in April 1983.<ref name=\"obnoxio\" /> The plot centered on Obnoxio the Clown as a villain and unlikely ally against the [[X-Men]].<ref name=\"obnoxio\" /> He and the group, at the [[X-Mansion]], 'team-up' against Eye Scream, a villain that can transform into various types of ice cream.\n\nThe sole issue of the comic book was written, illustrated, colored, and lettered by [[Alan Kupperberg]];<ref>Comic Collector live. [http://www.comiccollectorlive.com/LiveData/Issue.aspx?id=acf47b1c-3668-4a8b-952f-9de5123de7c4 Obnoxio The Clown #1.] Accessed November 2008.</ref> in a comment which Kupperberg attributes to [[Peter David]],<ref>[http://www.alankupperberg.com/comicbook.html Kupperberg interview] from ''[[Comic Book Artist]]'' #16, archived at AlanKupperberg.com</ref> and which David attributes to [[James Owsley]],<ref>[http://www.peterdavid.net/index.php/2010/05/07/not-in-any-store/ Not in Any Store\u2026], by Peter David, from [[Comics Buyer's Guide]] #1003, February 5, 1993; archived at PeterDavid.net</ref> the comic was described as \"Written, penciled, inked and lettered by Alan Kupperberg. Yes, it\u2019s untouched by human hands.\"\n\n==In other media==\n===Television===\n* Obnoxio makes a cameo appearance in the ''[[Hulk and the Agents of S.M.A.S.H.]]'' episode \"Fear Itself\", voiced by [[John DiMaggio]]. The Agents of S.M.A.S.H. receive old television signals including a TV show starring Obnoxio which freaks [[Rick Jones (comics)|A-Bomb]] out. He somewhat appears later in the episode as an part of an illusion caused by the [[Null (comics)|Null]] that releases people's fears where Null unleashes this illusion on A-Bomb.\n\n===Video games===\n* Android replicas of Obnoxio the Clown appears as a enemies during [[Wolverine]] levels in [[Spider-Man/X-Men: Arcade's Revenge]].\n\n* Though he is not seen in the game, Obnoxio the Clown is briefly mentioned in the [[Facebook]] game ''[[Marvel: Avengers Alliance]]''. Obnoxio the Clown is mentioned to have been murdered by the Circle of Eight.\n\n===Novel===\n* In the alternate reality depicted in the \"Doctor Doom: The Chaos Trilogy\" novels, written by Steven A. Roman, Obnoxio has a popular slapstick comedy show. Like anything on television, the show is approved by Doctor Doom's administration.{{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://daveslongbox.blogspot.com/2005/04/obnoxio-clown-marvel-comics-1983.html Obnoxio the Clown] - General information (blog).\n* [http://www.marvunapp.com/Appendix/iscrm.htm Marvel Appendix entry on Eye Scream, villain from the one-shot].\n\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1980]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Larry Hama]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\n[[Category:Fictional clowns]]\n\n\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}